Netball South Africa president Cecilia Molokwane and her executive members have taken a unanimous decision to suspend all planned netball activities scheduled to take place in March and April 2020 respectively effective immediately. CAPE TOWN - Following the address by President Cyril Ramaphosa on Sunday where he declared the coronavirus pandemic a national disaster and following what has been happening around the globe from various sporting codes, Netball South Africa president Cecilia Molokwane and her executive members have taken a unanimous decision to suspend all planned netball activities scheduled to take place in March and April 2020 respectively effective immediately. The affected events include the 2020 Telkom Netball League media launch and the under-21 national training camp. The decision was taken with the aim of protecting all stakeholders and partners. The executive committee will continue to monitor what is happening in the country and make decisions as the situation dictated. The team is expected to reconvene again in thirty days to assess the situation and inform members of the media and the public on the next steps. Further announcements regarding this will be made by 17 April 2020. National team players who are currently playing in Australia and England were in self-isolation following their respective leagues being suspended.